Class AbstractProductIon

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.iongen.impl.DefaultPeptideIon
      • uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.iongen.impl.AbstractProductIon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<ProductIon>, PeptideIon, ProductIon
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultProductIon

    public abstract class AbstractProductIon
extends DefaultPeptideIon
implements ProductIon, Comparable<ProductIon>
    Implement most of methods of ProductIon interface. This class implements Comparable interface, which can be storage into sorted collections based on cleavage position ascending order. This class Extends DefaultPeptideIon which inherit peptide ion methods: such as DefaultPeptideIon.getMass(), DefaultPeptideIon.getMassOverCharge(), and so on.
    Version:
    0.1-SNAPSHOT
    Author:
    Qingwei XU

    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractProductIon

        public AbstractProductIon(PrecursorIon precursorIon,
                  ProductIonType type,
                  int position,
                  Peptide peptide,
                  int charge)
        Create product ion instance. There are some constraints among the PrecursorIon, ProductIonType, cleavage position, and the ProductIon.

        Notice: Not suggest user to create a instance by calling construct method directly.

        Reference AbstractPrecursorIon.getProductIon(uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.mol.ProductIonType, int, int) see how to generate the product ion.
        Parameters:
        precursorIon - should not set null! Otherwise throw NullPointerException.
        type - should not set null! Otherwise throw NullPointerException.
        position - from [1..precursor.peptide.length-1]
        peptide - product ion peptide. should not set null! Otherwise throw NullPointerException.
        charge - from [1..3], should not great than precursor ion charges.
